</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="130">
Shell. Measurements (n = 6): SH 7.0-8.5 mm, SW 4.0-4.5 mm, HA 3.0-3.5, WA 2.0-2.5, Wh 6.0-7.0; approx. 1.8
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
higher than wide, thin, ovate-conic, fresh shells light yellowish, older shells straw coloured. Surface glossy, with widely spaced incised radial striations. The first whorl smooth, second whorl with 10-11distinct fine spiral lirae (Fig. 2A1), other whorls with widely spaced radial striations. Sides convex, suture impressed. Aperture nearly ovate, 1.7
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
higher than wide, margin simple and thick, columellar margin abruptly truncated, columella slightly curved.
</paragraph>
